Say "=== PROSE LANGUAGE ANALYSIS ===".
Say "".

Say "PROS:".
Say "- Extremely readable syntax that resembles plain English".
Say "- Easy to learn for beginners without programming experience".
Say "- Clear and intuitive control structures (if, repeat, etc.)".
Say "- Good for educational purposes and prototyping ideas".
Say "- Functions are supported with 'Define' and 'Call' keywords".
Say "- Supports variables, conditionals, loops, and basic math".
Say "".

Say "LIMITATIONS COMPARED TO PYTHON:".
Say "- Limited data structures (basic lists seem restricted)".
Say "- No support for comments (# symbols aren't recognized)".
Say "- Limited string manipulation functions".
Say "- Less flexible syntax - very strict English-like sentences".
Say "- Limited library ecosystem compared to Python".
Say "- Performance likely slower than compiled languages".
Say "- More verbose for complex operations".
Say "- Limited third-party package support".
Say "".

Say "USE CASES WHERE PROSE SHINES:".
Say "- Teaching programming concepts to beginners".
Say "- Rapid prototyping of simple algorithms".
Say "- Domain-specific applications where readability is key".
Say "- Accessibility for non-programmers to express logic".
Say "".

Say "SUMMARY:".
Say "Prose is an innovative approach to programming that prioritizes".
Say "readability and accessibility. While it may not match Python's".
Say "performance or flexibility, it fills a unique niche for".
Say "making programming more approachable to non-programmers.".
Say "It's a creative contribution to the programming language space!".